                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72115/3357</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MJVA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-01T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British Embassy here informs the Department that the representatives in
                    Peking of the Allied Governments excepting the Belgian Minister sent to their
                    Governments a telegram recommending the adoption of a proposal made by China to
                    intern about 120 enemy subjects in a temple about 40 miles from Peking. The
                    British Government is prepared to accept the proposal. When these Ministers
                    excepting the Belgian are advised that their Governments have agreed to the
                    proposal you are instructed to inform the Chinese Government that the American
                    Government also agrees to it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
